    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 18 October 1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>The bearer of the letter did not wait for him to send a letter when they
                            received news that the new Pope has been elected: it is Cardinal
                            Alessandro Farnese. Lodovico Gritti is rumoured to have been killed by
                            his Romanian (Dacian) compatriots from Transylvania. If only they knew
                            what the Sultan was planning regarding the Hungarian affairs; the
                            French, the Veneti, and the Pope only know some details. Cristoforo
                            Doria has gone to Syria with two boats and occupied Tyre, then he went
                            over to Palestine; it is known exactly how big a devastation he has
                            inflicted on the Turkish forces. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Camillus Gilinus Nicolao Olao suo salutem. </p>
                <p>Commodum tabellarius recesserat, cum nobis allatum fuit cardinalem
                        <persName>Farnesium</persName><note type="critic">Alessandro Farnese
                        (1468–1549) was elected on 13 October, 1534 and became Pope Paul III. On the
                        election see Ghilino’s previous letter: Ep.
                        514.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15341012_2</ref> pontificem designatum esse,
                    omniaque <placeName>Romae</placeName> pacata. Fama nos tenet
                        <persName>Griteum</persName><note type="critic">Lodovico Gritti was killed
                        on 29 September, 1534.</note> Turcae a Dacis tuis civibus interfectum. </p>
                <pb/>
                <p>Utinam prius caesaris Turcarum sententiam super rebus Hungaricis
                    perscrutati essent, multa certe ex eo de Gallis et fortasse de Venetis et
                    pontifice ad rem nostram cognovissent, sed Deus optimus maximus operam dabit, ut
                    aequi et iniqui intelligant, caesarum nostrorum <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >illustrissimarum</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr"
                        >illustrissimam</add> domum sibi oppido curae esse. <persName>Christophorus
                        Auria</persName>,<note type="critic">Cristoforo Doria.</note>
                    <persName>principis Auriae</persName><note type="critic">Andrea Doria.</note>
                    nepos ex sorore, qui pyraticam faciebat, in <placeName>Syriam</placeName> cum
                    duabus actuariis navibus descendit et capta <placeName>Tyro</placeName><note
                        type="critic">Tyre.</note> depopulata et incensa transmittebat in
                    Palestinam, certum habemus illum in hac expeditione IIII triremes et fustes V <choice>
                        <orig>Turcis</orig>
                        <supplied>Turcos</supplied>
                    </choice> intercepisse, et magnis divitiis auctum. Vale et me <persName>Virgini
                        Lucretiae</persName><note type="critic"> Lucretia Caballis (vom
                        Ross).</note> plurimum commenda. </p>
                <p><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> XV. Kalendas Novembris anno Domini
                    1534.</p>
            </div>
